      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 54,
      "message": "You can write this function as one expression in more functional way like this:\n\n    fun isValid(message: VesMessage): Validated<NonEmptyList<ValidationError>, CommonEventHeader> =\n            HeaderValidator(message.header).let { validator ->\n                validator.parallelValidate(\n                        validator.validate(HeaderReader.EVENT_LISTENER_VERSION_READ, message.header.vesEventListenerVersion),\n                        headerRequiredFieldDescriptors.map { \n                            validator.validate(HeaderReader.REQUIRED_FIELD_READ, it)\n                        }\n                )\n            }\n\nAlso, if all you're doing with the message is extracting its header, it would be better to make this method take CommonEventHeader as argument instead of VesMessage",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3081,
        "name": "Jakub Dudycz",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jakub.dudycz@nokia.com",
        "username": "dudini1"
      },
      "updated": "2018-12-07 08:56:38.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
